	Apparently, route/geographical suggestions are on the rise.  In fact, a
	couple discussions on this list indicate that only the US considers
	"organization" preferrable.

I apologise if I gave this impression.  It's not what I meant to say.

The eventual direction of X.400 is VERY oriented to organizations.  After
the top level country domain, the second level is the organization.  This
is very similar to the ARPA domain scheme, where the second level is
usually the organization.

The thing that X.400 does not use is the "type of organization" information,
that is, the notions "this is an EDUcational organization" or "this is
a COMpany."  They just have you send mail to something like "John Smith
in the Computer Science Department of UCLA in the United States" (or the
equivalent way of writing this down in binary.)

The X.400 interest in geography extends ONLY to the country level.  Within
the country you use local conventions, although they do provide hooks for
use of local geography if the country prefers.

	Mark

